{
  "texts": [
    "It is necessary to identify hospital-specific factors that could influence this outcome.",
    "The reduction in Triage Time, Door-to-INR Notification Time, CT-to-Arterial Puncture, and Door-to-Arterial Puncture Time in the AI groups implies the potential for AI interventions to enhance stroke team responsiveness, thereby potentially minimizing adverse clinical outcomes and optimizing the treatment window for stroke care.",
    "Conversely, the patient's LKW to Time-of-Arrival OR of 1.15 (95% CI: 0.83 -1.59, p = 0.409) and DIDO Time OR of 1.19 (95% CI: 0.21 -6.88, p = 0.848) and inter-facility Transfer Times between primary and comprehensive stroke centers an OR of 0.98 (95% CI: 0.73 -1.32, p = 0.893), demonstrated a relatively marginal and statistically insignificant discrepancy between AI and non-AI methodologies.",
    "Similarly, Door to CTA Time, with an OR of 0.77 (95% CI: 0.37 -1.60, p = 0.489), displayed a wide range in 95% of comparable populations (0.00 to 4419.82).",
    "There seems to be no apparent explanation for AI to reduce these times, given that AI is typically initiated after the completion of the CT scan."
  ]
}